Product Requirements Document (PRD)

Project: Skandasramam.com
Version: 2.1
Date: September 03, 2025
Document Owner: Product Team
Status: Draft

1. Executive Summary

Vision Statement:
To create a digital spiritual hub that connects devotees worldwide with timeless traditions, making ashram experiences accessible, inclusive, and modern while preserving their sanctity.

Problem Statement:

Traditional ashrams struggle with limited digital presence.

Manual booking processes create friction for devotees.

No centralized source for event schedules or poojas.

Difficulty managing capacity and resources.

Solution Overview:
Ashram Fullstack is a comprehensive web application to:

Provide intuitive event discovery and booking.

Enable digital spiritual calendar management.

Create seamless devotee experience with reminders & follow-ups.

Empower administrators with robust back-office tools.

Market Context:
India has ~500M spiritual participants annually, but <10% have access to online booking or event info. Skandasramam.com aims to bridge this digital gap.

2. Product Goals & Success Metrics
2.1 Primary Goals

Digital Transformation: Modernize ashram operations.

Community Engagement: Increase participation by 40% in 6 months.

Operational Efficiency: Cut manual booking time by 80%.

User Satisfaction: 4.5+ star ratings + NPS > 50 in 3 months.

2.2 Key KPIs

Engagement: Monthly active users, session duration.

Conversion: >85% booking completion, attendance rate.

Technical: Load time <2s, uptime 99.9%.

Business: Revenue per booking, repeat visitor rate, donation conversion.

2.3 Success Criteria

1,000+ registered users in 3 months.

100+ bookings/month by month 6.

Mobile responsiveness: Lighthouse score 95+.

Zero critical security issues.

3. User Personas & Journey
3.1 Personas

Devotee: 25–65, moderate tech. Wants to discover, book poojas, get reminders.

Administrator: 30–55, basic tech. Wants easy event & resource management.

Casual Visitor: 20–70, browsing info, exploring offerings.

Remote Devotee (NEW): International/NRI, cannot attend physically but wants to sponsor poojas, join livestreams, receive prasad.

Accessibility-First User (NEW): Senior citizen with low vision/hearing, requiring high contrast, large fonts, voice assistance.

3.2 Journey

Discovery: Landing → Browse events/poojas.

Exploration: Details → Calendar → Compare.

Decision: Select event → Review.

Booking: Fill form → (Future: Payment) → Confirmation.

Participation: Reminders → Attend or livestream.

Follow-up: Feedback → Sponsorship → Community engagement.

4. Feature Specifications
4.1 Frontend (Next.js + Builder.io)

Landing Page (Builder Hero + Feature Blocks): Ashram mission, quick access to events/poojas/calendar, testimonials, location map.

Events Module: Search/filter, infinite scroll, related events, share options.

Poojas Module: Daily/special, significance, availability calendar, sponsorship option.

Booking Widget: Multi-step form, real-time availability, cancellation policy, SMS/Email confirmation.

Future: Payment, group bookings, waitlists, recurring bookings.

Event Calendar: Monthly/weekly/daily view, quick booking, export to Google/Outlook, festival highlighting.

Notifications: Toast + PWA push notifications.

4.2 Backend

APIs: /events, /poojas, /bookings, /users, /notifications.

Database (Postgres/Prisma): Events, poojas, bookings, users, availability, donations, notifications.

Integrations:

Email: SendGrid/AWS SES

SMS: Twilio

Payments: Razorpay/Stripe (Phase 2)

Calendar sync: Google API

Analytics: GA4

5. Technical Architecture

Frontend: Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, React Query, React Hook Form, Builder.io CMS.
Backend: Node.js 18+, Express, PostgreSQL, Prisma ORM, Redis cache, Supabase Auth.
Hosting: Vercel (frontend), Render/AWS (backend), Supabase/AWS RDS (DB).
Security: JWT auth, role-based access, CSP, HTTPS, rate limiting.
Performance: CDN for static, image optimization, caching, background jobs, DB pooling.

6. UX & Design

Principles: Simplicity, accessibility, spiritual aesthetics.

Brand: Warm colors, temple motifs, calming typography.

Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA, screen reader support, font scaling, voice guidance.

Mobile-first: 320px upwards, touch-friendly.

Localization-ready: Hindi, Sanskrit, Tamil; expandable to regional languages.

7. Testing & QA

Unit: Components, API, utilities.

Integration: API, DB, services.

E2E: User journeys (Playwright).

Accessibility: axe/pa11y audits.

Performance: Lighthouse, k6 load testing.

Resilience: Chaos testing during festival load spikes.

8. Deployment & Ops

Environments: Dev → Staging → Prod.

Process: GitHub Actions CI/CD, zero-downtime deploys, rollback migrations.

Monitoring: Sentry, APM, backups, RTO < 1h, RPO < 15m.

Ops Cost Estimate: $3–5k/month.

9. Roadmap

Phase 1 (Months 1–3): MVP — Core booking, events, poojas, calendar, notifications.
Phase 2 (Months 4–6): Payments, Admin Dashboard, profiles, donation sponsorship, volunteer-friendly tools.
Phase 3 (Months 7–12): Multi-language, livestreaming, community forums, advanced analytics.
Year 2+: Multi-location, AI recommendations, IoT smart capacity, blockchain donation tracking.

10. Risks & Mitigations

Technical: DB scaling → Optimize queries, Redis caching.

Business: Low adoption → SEO, community outreach, unique value prop.

Operational: Key personnel dependency → Cross-training, documentation.

11. Budget & Timeline

Phase 0 Prototype (3–4 weeks): Marketing site + event listings + booking form ($20–30k).

Phase 1–3 Total: $200–270k (as per v2.0).

Resources: Full-stack dev, frontend dev, backend dev, UI/UX, QA (part-time), PM.

12. Conclusion

Skandasramam.com is not just a booking engine but a spiritual digital ecosystem. By combining modern UX, inclusive design, and robust backend, it will strengthen community bonds, improve access, and enable global participation in ashram traditions.